    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> ok you saw a cave troll and a swarm and a few difficult cards, but they aren`t that usefull here.<br>
<br>
Sites:<br>
·Hobbiton Party Fields: Play Bilbo Exerting Pippin and with practically everyone was invited play all your hobbit allies.<br>
·Rivendell Terrace: Play Boromir to draw a card, and use Athelas to throw away those nazgul companion conditions.<br>
·Moria Stairway: I love Scavengers with scimitars they are really cool and here they get a damade +1 and Merry is better to.<br>
·Valley of the Silverlode: Heal all your tired hobbits.I like it more than Dimrill Dale who knows why??.<br>
·Anduin Wilderland: Here is where you usually make a big swarm and sometimes win, because archery can`t kill your orcs.<br>
·Shores of Nen Hithoel: this is a great site 8 it stops the fellowship because you always have more tha 5 minions on site 8.<br>
·Summit of Amon Hen: On site 9 you always need more minions because there`s a lot of twilight so drawing an extra card for each burden isn`t that bad.<br>
<br>
Free Peoples:<br>
<br>
Frodo is here to heal your allies. Merry is your main fighter he must get a hobbit sword as soon as he can, and a stone trolls to. Sam is great on nazgul decks he take all the burdens and tha gaffer heals him. Pippin is always ready to fight when you get a big minion and everybody is overhelmed. Bilbo with your tales removes condition from the support area and Athelas from the companions. With O Elbereth! Gilthoniel! you are safe against nazguls. And with Thror`s Map you get into site 7 with out discarding your allies.<br>
<br>
Shadow: <br>
<br>
Armories and Relics of Moria are great for scimitars and scavengers to. Swarms are really important but you can play without it and the Cave Troll can be changed by a big minion. <br>
